agment = '}'\n  private static def listGetterFragment = '('\n  private static def listIndexStartFragment = '['\n  private static def listIndexEndFragment = ']'\n  private static def space = ' '\n\n  def static escapePath(key, PathFragmentEscaper... pathFragmentEscapers) {\n    def pathFragments = key.split(\"(?<=\\\\')\")\n    for (int i = 0; i < pathFragments.size(); i++) {\n      String pathFragment = pathFragments[i]\n      if (!pathFragment?.endsWith(\"'\") || pathFragment?.contains(\"**\")) {\n        def dotFragments = pathFragment.split(\"\\\\.\")\n        for (int k = 0; k < dotFragments.size(); k++) {\n          String dotFragment = dotFragments[k]\n          for (int j = 0; j < pathFragmentEscapers.length; j++) {\n            def escaper = pathFragmentEscapers[j]\n            if (escaper.shouldEscape(dotFragment)) {\n              dotFragments[k] = escaper.escape(dotFragments[k].trim())\n              break;\n            }\n          }\n\n        }\n        pathFragments[i] = dotFragments.join(\".\")\n      }\n    }\n    pathFragments.join(\"\")\n  }\n\n  def static hyphen() {\n    new HyphenQuoteFragmentEscaper() {\n      @Override\n      boolean shouldEscape(String pathFragment) {\n        !pathFragment.startsWith(\"'\") && !pathFragment.endsWith(\"'\") && pathFragment.contains('-') && !pathFragment.contains('[-') && !containsAny(pathFragment, [closureStartFragment, closureEndFragment, listGetterFragment])\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  def static properties() {\n    new GetAtPathFragmentEscaper() {\n      @Override\n      boolean shouldEscape(String pathFragment) {\n        !pathFragment.startsWith(\"'\") && !pathFragment.endsWith(\"'\") && pathFragment.contains('properties') && !containsAny(pathFragment, [closureStartFragment, closureEndFragment, listGetterFragment, listIndexStartFragment, space, listIndexEndFragment])\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  def static classKeyword() {\n    new GetAtPathFragmentEscaper() {\n      @Override\n      boolean shouldEscape(String pathFragment) {\n        !pathFragment.startsWith(\"'\") && !pathFragment.endsWith(\"'\") && pathFragment.contains('class') && !containsAny(pathFragment, [closureStartFragment, closureEndFragment, listGetterFragment, listIndexStartFragment, space, listIndexEndFragment])\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  def static attributeGetter() {\n    new EndToEndQuoteFragmentEscaper() {\n      @Override\n      boolean shouldEscape(String pathFragment) {\n        pathFragment.startsWith(\"@\") && !pathFragment.endsWith(\"'\") && !containsAny(pathFragment, [closureStartFragment, closureEndFragment, space])\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  def static doubleStar() {\n    new EndToEndQuoteFragmentEscaper() {\n      @Override\n      boolean shouldEscape(String pathFragment) {\n        pathFragment == \"**\"\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  def static colon() {\n    new HyphenQuoteFragmentEscaper() {\n      @Override\n      boolean shouldEscape(String pathFragment) {\n        !pathFragment.startsWith(\"'\") && !pathFragment.endsWith(\"'\") && pathFragment.contains(':') && !containsAny(pathFragment, [closureStartFragment, closureEndFragment, listGetterFragment])\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  def static integer() {\n    new EndToEndQuoteFragmentEscaper() {\n      @Override\n      boolean shouldEscape(String pathFragment) {\n        (startsWithDigit(pathFragment) || NumberUtils.isDigits(pathFragment)) && !containsAny(pathFragment, [closureStartFragment, closureEndFragment, space, listGetterFragment, listIndexStartFragment, listIndexEndFragment])\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  private static boolean startsWithDigit(def pathFragment) {\n    if (StringUtils.isEmpty(pathFragment)) {\n      return false\n    }\n    Character.isDigit(pathFragment.charAt(0))\n  }\n\n  def static String generateWhitespace(int number) {\n    if (number < 1) {\n      \"\"\n    }\n    StringBuilder builder = new StringBuilder();\n    for (int i = 0; i < number; i++) {\n      builder.append(' ');\n    }\n    return builder.toString();\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Copied from Apache commons lang (String utils)\n   */\n  private static boolean containsAny(String str, searchChars) {\n    if (str == null || str.length() == 0 || searchChars == null || searchChars.isEmpty()) {\n      return false;\n    }\n    for (int i = 0; i < str.length(); i++) {\n      char ch = str.charAt(i);\n      for (int j = 0; j < searchChars.size(); j++) {\n        if (searchChars[j] == ch) {\n          return true;\n        }\n      }\n    }\n    return false;\n  }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1779528013505}, {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_7J3d9VDp0M76Y2LvGXX2twaT|fc_09464b20a62d7248016a11714d493c819f9492202e379f68dd", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage io_rest_assured.rest_assured_common\n\nimport io.restassured.internal.common.assertion.AssertionSupport\nimport io.restassured.internal.common.assertion.PathFragmentEscaper\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\n\npublic class AssertionSupportAnonymous1Test {\n    @Test\n    void escapesHyphenatedPathFragments() {\n        PathFragmentEscaper escaper = AssertionSupport.hyphen() as PathFragmentEscaper\n\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape('item-name')).isTrue()\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape(\"'item-name'\")).isFalse()\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape('items[-1]')).isFalse()\n        assertThat(escaper.escape('item-name[0]')).isEqualTo(\"'item-name'[0]\")\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1779528013505}, {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_kxTujqGTEUZH8jpVpDyj4TZG|fc_09464b20a62d7248016a11714d4944819fa99ef279b3c10270", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage io_rest_assured.rest_assured_common\n\nimport io.restassured.internal.common.assertion.AssertionSupport\nimport io.restassured.internal.common.assertion.PathFragmentEscaper\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodType\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\n\npublic class AssertionSupportAnonymous2Test {\n    @Test\n    void escapesPropertiesPathFragmentsWithGetAtSyntax() {\n        PathFragmentEscaper escaper = AssertionSupport.properties() as PathFragmentEscaper\n\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape('properties')).isTrue()\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape('response.properties')).isTrue()\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape(\"'properties'\")).isFalse()\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape('properties[0]')).isFalse()\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape('properties value')).isFalse()\n        assertThat(escaper.escape('properties')).isEqualTo(\"getAt('properties')\")\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void appliesPropertiesEscaperWhenEscapingFullPath() {\n        String escapedPath = AssertionSupport.escapePath(\n                'response.properties.value',\n                AssertionSupport.properties()) as String\n\n        assertThat(escapedPath).isEqualTo(\"response.getAt('properties').value\")\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void resolvesTypesThroughGeneratedClassLiteralHelperOnPropertiesEscaperClass() {\n        PathFragmentEscaper escaper = AssertionSupport.properties() as PathFragmentEscaper\n        Class<?> escaperType = escaper.getClass()\n        MethodHandles.Lookup lookup = MethodHandles.privateLookupIn(escaperType, MethodHandles.lookup())\n        MethodHandle classLookup = lookup.findStatic(escaperType, 'class$', MethodType.methodType(Class, String))\n\n        Class<?> resolvedType = classLookup.invokeWithArguments('java.lang.String') as Class<?>\n\n        assertThat(resolvedType).isSameAs(String)\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1779528013505}, {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_QJ84O4RtutoQqfJGF9dw9Rrz|fc_09464b20a62d7248016a11714d4948819fa18d44903a9f5dd9", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage io_rest_assured.rest_assured_common\n\nimport io.restassured.internal.common.assertion.AssertionSupport\nimport io.restassured.internal.common.assertion.PathFragmentEscaper\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\n\npublic class AssertionSupportAnonymous3Test {\n    @Test\n    void escapesClassKeywordPathFragmentsWithGetAtSyntax() {\n        PathFragmentEscaper escaper = AssertionSupport.classKeyword() as PathFragmentEscaper\n\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape('class')).isTrue()\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape('response.class')).isTrue()\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape(\"'class'\")).isFalse()\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape('class[0]')).isFalse()\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape('class value')).isFalse()\n        assertThat(escaper.escape('class')).isEqualTo(\"getAt('class')\")\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void appliesClassKeywordEscaperWhenEscapingFullPath() {\n        String escapedPath = AssertionSupport.escapePath(\n                'response.class.name',\n                AssertionSupport.classKeyword()) as String\n\n        assertThat(escapedPath).isEqualTo(\"response.getAt('class').name\")\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void leavesClassKeywordFragmentsUntouchedWhenTheyArePartOfUnsupportedExpressions() {\n        PathFragmentEscaper escaper = AssertionSupport.classKeyword() as PathFragmentEscaper\n\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape('class[0]')).isFalse()\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape('class value')).isFalse()\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape('class.find { it.simpleName }')).isFalse()\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape('class()')).isFalse()\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1779528013505}, {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_8xN9GZLEtM1ZdIDLKLV6pxnX|fc_09464b20a62d7248016a11714d4950819fba46e4091dbcf8a6", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage io_rest_assured.rest_assured_common\n\nimport io.restassured.internal.common.assertion.AssertionSupport\nimport io.restassured.internal.common.assertion.PathFragmentEscaper\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\n\npublic class AssertionSupportAnonymous4Test {\n    @Test\n    void escapesAttributeGetterPathFragmentsWithQuotedSyntax() {\n        PathFragmentEscaper escaper = AssertionSupport.attributeGetter() as PathFragmentEscaper\n\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape('@id')).isTrue()\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape('@type')).isTrue()\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape(\"'@id'\")).isFalse()\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape('@id value')).isFalse()\n        assertThat(escaper.shouldEscape('@id.find { it != null }')).isFalse()\n        assertThat(escaper.escape('@id')).isEqualTo(\"'@id'\")\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void appliesAttributeGetterEscaperWhenEscapingFullPath() {\n        String escapedPath = AssertionSupport.escapePath(\n                'response.@id.item.@type',\n                AssertionSupport.attributeGetter()) as String\n\n        assertThat(escapedPath).isEqualTo(\"response.'@id'.item.'@type'\")\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "time