ide whether to retry the same class or move on.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:449:Composite strategies (run a primary workflow, then refine dynamic-access coverage):\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:456:#### Running a dynamic-access strategy\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:478:For the detailed function-level notes and sequence diagram, see `docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md`.\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2523:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage from the stored run metrics stats block.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2539:    covered_calls = int(dynamic_access.get(\"coveredCalls\", 0) or 0)\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2553:    \"\"\"Resolve the dynamic-access coverage report path for a new-library issue.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2559:        \"dynamic-access\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2560:        \"dynamic-access-coverage.json\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2565:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage directly from the generated report as a fallback.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2695:        \"Analyze the generated tests, metadata, stats, and dynamic-access report in this repository. \"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2699:        \"- Explain briefly why dynamic-access coverage is missing or still very low.\\n\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2718:        f\"Automation completed for `{claimed_issue.issue_coordinates}`, but dynamic-access coverage remains \"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2720:        \"This suggests the generated tests are not exercising the required dynamic-access paths well enough.\\n\\n\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2722:        \"- Inspect the generated tests and compare them with the dynamic-access report to find uncovered call sites.\\n\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:3489:            pipeline_argv.append(\"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\")\nforge/forge_metadata.py:5672:        \"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:5675:            \"Forwarded to the new-library pipeline. Keeps generated tests for dynamic-access \"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:5676:            \"strategies e